{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 42,
  "title": "第四十二章（中和）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "道生一。一生二。二生三。三生萬物。"
    },
    {
      "text": "萬物負陰而抱陽。中氣以為和。"
    },
    {
      "text": "天下之所惡，唯「孤」 「寡」 「不穀」。而王公以自名也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "勿或：損之而益，益之而損。故人之所教，夕議而教人。"
    },
    {
      "text": "故強良者不得死。我將以為學父。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 5,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "一生陰與陽也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 10,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "陰陽生和、清、濁三氣，分為天地人也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天地人共生萬物也，天施地化，人長養之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 4,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物無不負陰而向陽，迴心而就日。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 14,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物中皆有元氣，得以和柔，若胸中有藏，骨中有髓，草木中有空虛與氣通，故得久生也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 28,
          "end": 28
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "孤寡不轂者，不祥之名，而王公以為稱者，處謙卑，法空虛和柔。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "引之不得，推之必還。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "夫增高者志崩，貪富者致患。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 28,
          "end": 29
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂眾人所教，去弱為強，去柔為剛。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言我教眾人，使去強為弱，去柔為剛。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "強粱者，謂不信玄妙，背叛道德，不從經教，尚勢任力也。不得其死者，為天命所絕，兵刃所伐，王法所殺，不得以壽命死。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "父，使也。老子以強梁之人為教，誡之始也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 17,
          "end": 17
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物萬形，其歸一也，何由致一，由於無也。由無乃一，一可謂無，已謂之一，豈得無言乎。有言有一，非二如何？有一有二，遂生乎三，從無之有，數盡乎斯，過此以往，非道之流，故萬物之生，吾知其主，雖有萬形，沖氣一焉。百姓有心，異國殊風，而得一者，王侯主焉。以一為主，一何可舍，愈多愈遠，損則近之，損之至盡，乃得其極。既謂之一，猶乃至三，況本不一而道可近乎，損之而益，豈虛言也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 25,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "我之非強使人從之也，而用夫自然，舉其至理，順之必吉，違之必凶。故人相教，違之自取其凶也，亦如我之教人，勿違之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 15,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "强梁則必不得其死。人相教為强梁，則必如我之教人不當為强梁也。舉其強梁不得其死以教邪。若云順吾教之必吉也，故得其違教之徒，適可以為教父也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
